Elytra arcuate, basal margin slightly concave, apex gently rounded and emarginate laterally; striae with deep circular punctures, diameter longer than distance between punctures; intervals: with evenly shaped and distributed punctures; punctures with median keel dividing each puncture and with minute setae slightly off-center on keel (Fig. 28); first interval dilated behind declivity to apex, with fine punctures and appressed, minute setae from declivity to apex; intervals four and six connate and fused at declivity (Fig. 24); humeri convex, limited by striae six to eight and intervals six to nine. Sclerolepidia along dorsal margin of metaventrite appearing closer to digitate type 2A (Figs 31, 32), in which sclerolepidia are divided into two distinct lobes, with each lobe divided into several short digits (
Lyal et al. 2006
).
